But let vs see how the knight goeth forward in his tale; after he hath tolde vs of these clowds, mists and darknes, that then raygned, he addeth these woords: whereunto (sayth he) was added, and wherwith was mixed, all bloody and sauadg cruelty agaynst those that desired knowledge and were any way inlightened by Gods grace, Manifeste vntruthes. with a glimering or smale insight into true religion. For though it were but only a desire to read vpō the holy booke of God;
ether the olde or new testament, then heretique was his title, heresy was his fault;
•• d for this was he called before the Romish Cleargy to receyue their censure, and
•• ch neuer departed from their clowtches till they had brandeled them to the
• aughter.
